- A specialized pool used for timing-related tasks, such as running background maintenance or recurring events

- Methods of Execution:
schedule: Runs a task once after a specific delay

scheduleAtFixedRate: Executes tasks repeatedly based on the start time of the previous execution
                     (e.g., every 10 minutes regardless of how long the task takes, unless the task duration
                     exceeds the interval)

scheduleWithFixedDelay: Executes tasks repeatedly with a fixed delay measured from the completion time of the
                        previous execution
